  "kind": "note",
  "title": "Aurelius, Meditations §aur_04_xxxviii: Even as if any of the gods should tell thee, Thou shalt certainly die to-morr...",
  "body": "Even as if any of the gods should tell thee, Thou shalt certainly die to-morrow, or next day, thou wouldst not, except thou wert extremely base and pusillanimous, take it for a great benefit, rather to die the next day after, than to-morrow; (for alas, what is the difference!) so, for the same reason, think it no great matter to die rather many years after, than the very next day.",
  "source": {
    "label": "Marcus Aurelius, Meditations (c. AD 170)",
